    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, our lineup leans heavily on high-floor performers facing vulnerable arms, anchored by **Bryson Stott** (72.46) and **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (71.77). **Bryson Stott** is our top play; his favorable matchup against Luis Severino, combined with a +13% platoon edge and wind blowing out, maximizes his ceiling. Similarly, **Matt Chapman** (70.21) remains a high-leverage start, as he benefits from a weak opponent in Walker Buehler (4.91 xERA) and environmental factors that elevate his power profile. **Gleyber Torres** (67.52) also draws a strong projection, capitalizing on a significant +13% platoon advantage against Jovani Mor\u00e1n. \n\nThe optimizer\u2019s preference for speed and efficiency kept a few tough calls on the bench, specifically **Jonathan Aranda** (51.11) and **Daulton Varsho** (50.85). While **Jonathan Aranda** holds a strong xwOBA, he couldn't crack the lineup due to Kevin Gausman\u2019s ability to suppress production, despite a favorable platoon split. **Daulton Varsho** was also heavily considered for his elite sprint speed and base-stealing potential against Drew Rasmussen, but he ultimately fell short to our higher-scoring outfielders, **Jung Hoo Lee** (65.65) and **Wenceel Perez** (65.10), who benefit from superior lineup positioning and current pitching volatility.\n\nRisks today are centered on the \"Lineup Pending\" status for all starters, which introduces volatility in projected batting order points. Specifically, **Will Smith** (53.91) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (53.69) are hovering near our marginal floor; if either drops significantly in the order once lineups are official, their efficiency scores will slide further, potentially triggering a bench decision. We are betting heavily on the weakness of Walker Buehler, which provides a massive +19% SP skill boost to **Luis Arraez**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, and **Matt Chapman**, turning what would be a mediocre day into a potentially high-output offensive session.",
